  "body": "On *BSD systems, we can `open(2)` a directory and directly `read(2)` from it due to an old tradition.  We should avoid doing so by explicitly calling `fstat(2)` to check the type of the opened file.\n\nOpening a directory as a module file can't always be avoided.  Even when there's no \"path\" attribute trick involved, there can always be a _directory_ named `my_module.rs`.\n\nIncidentally, remove unnecessary mutability of `&self` from `io::fs::File::stat()`.\n",
